PS: numenorean, i do play for fun, it isnt fun to be lfg for an hour though <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uphread01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phread01</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.usinternet.com/users/alientro/phread0160.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/10/01 8:46:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.usinternet.com/users/alientro/phread0160.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor sad, nerfed Paladins</span><hr size=1> Okay, not trying to piss anybody off, but the reason paladins have a bad rep in upper end groups is because so many paladins have no clue how to help the groups they join.<br>
<br>
And no, this doesn't just mean use your stun, and it doesn't just mean heal in downtime, and it doesn't just mean any one thing.  It means that every group is different, and quite frankly, Paladins are capable of filling a LOT of holes in the group, as long as your group knows what you are doing and what role you are filling.<br>
<br>
The other problem is that there are so many pl'd/ebayed idiots in the game, that they don't have a clue how to play their characters, much less someone else's.  If you're grouped with a moron that thinks his entire job is to stand/cast/sit/repeat, how do you think he's going to have a clue what another class brings to the table?<br>
<br>
So the perception is, among the young and young at brain, that paladins are weak warriors with weak heals and weak buffs.  And that perception has been around since before kunark came out.  Remember that the next time you're in a group and the only thing you're doing is trying to deal melee damage, cast a few stuns, and maybe throw out some heals and buffs, you are part of the problem, not the solution.<br>
<br>
And by the way, i don't want a horse as a pet, i want a squire =).  And give him a hump on his back and a bad eye.  And cool pet names like Fetchit, or Diesforyou, that would make me grin. <p>Phread
